RT @GDCE_Official: Congratulations to all winners! 🎉 
Well deserved 👏 and a big shoutout to @CrowdHackio for hosting the HackOnXDC Hackathon! 

🚀 Let’s #BuildOnXDC  #XDC @XinFin_Official @CrowdHackio

Congratulations to all winners! 🎉 
Well deserved 👏 and a big shoutout to @CrowdHackio for hosting the HackOnXDC Hackathon! 

🚀 Let’s #BuildOnXDC  #XDC @XinFin_Official @CrowdHackio

We are very excited to announce the winners of our 1st HackOnXDC hackathon event.  We appreciate all Teams for coming out to #hack and hope to see all of your projects launch on the #XDCNetwork.  

A strong handshake goes out to @GDCE_Official and @CrowdHackio for all their support and always @XinFin_Official for supporting this and so many other hackathons to increase the development of dApps on the XDC Network.  

WINNERS: Trade Sync- Mobile SDK- TokenX

1st Place:  Trade Sync -  An enterprise solution for trade finance.  Creating efficiencies for exporters using DLT, AI, Hyper-Productive flows, building counter party registries with deep provenance and composable tokenization to keep the integrity at each layer while transferring the ownership.  For MSME's, this technology opens up many negotiable instruments and broader financial access. 

2nd Place:  Mobile SDK - Simplifying Web2--> Web3 adoption.  This SDK eliminates all the complexities that users are going through at the moment with the wallet (Metamask, XDCPay, etc). User has to remember the seed phrase and when they using any application, they must sign a transaction, the application has to give control to another app to do the same.  With this SDK we are eliminating these steps and the user would be able to sign and verify, send, etc in the same application.

3rd Place:  TokenX -  We offer an interactive no-code platform that allows users to create a NFT collection. We provide a simple interface to airdrop NFT's just by giving JSON of addresses.  User can also share the claimable link to mint NFT at the user’s convenience. We also provide dev tooling to airdrop created NFTs in batch through ready-to-use API. There are lots of actual use cases for communities, DAOs and institutions.  

Honorable Mention:  Outre Finance - Users are able to create loan offers and requests to borrow or lend to one another on their own terms.  68% of loans in the alternative lending market in Africa are P2P loans. With Outre P2P users are able to offer or request loans from each other at their own terms. Outre Finance helps with monitoring the Credit scores of users and only recommending matches to users in order to minimize the risk of default among users. This feature is very useful for those who survive on day loans to run small businesses for purposes such as inventory purchases. This product greatly reduces the cost of loans as it democratizes lending and also opens other earning avenues for users through interest.

Keep your eyes open for all the up and coming dApps building on the XDC Network. The Future is bright!

RT @invest_answers: To the Esteemed Unions and Government of Sweden,

I am writing to express my deep concern regarding the ongoing efforts to pressure #Tesla into unionizing its workforce in Sweden. While I understand the importance of unions and their role in protecting the rights of workers, I believe that the current approach being taken is misguided and could have detrimental consequences for both Tesla and Sweden as a whole.

Tesla, as a global company with a strong reputation for innovation and efficiency, has built its success on a foundation of non-unionized labor. This model has allowed the company to remain nimble, adaptable, and competitive in a rapidly changing industry. Demanding that Tesla abandon this model in favor of unionized labor would represent a significant departure from the company's core principles and could undermine its ability to thrive in the global marketplace.

Moreover, setting a precedent of forcing foreign companies to adopt Swedish union practices could have a chilling effect on future investment in Sweden. Businesses, both domestic and international, may become hesitant to establish operations in a country where labor relations are unpredictable and subject to arbitrary demands. This could lead to a decline in economic activity and job opportunities for Swedish workers.

In addition to these economic concerns, the current unionization efforts could also accelerate the development of automated technologies that could replace human workers. As unions push for higher wages and stricter working conditions, companies will be increasingly motivated to seek alternatives that are more cost-effective and less susceptible to unionization. This could lead to a significant loss of jobs in the automotive industry and other sectors that rely on human labor.

I urge the unions and the government of Sweden to tread very carefully in their dealings with Tesla. While the protection of workers' rights is undoubtedly important, it must not come at the expense of Sweden's economic competitiveness and its ability to attract foreign investment. A more constructive approach would be to engage in dialogue with Tesla to find common ground and solutions that benefit both the company and its employees.

Thank you for your time and consideration.

Sincerely, james 
cc @elonmusk

RT @S4mmyEth: Disney is coming to Web3.

Dapper Labs is partnering with the $159B entertainment conglomerate to bring Web3 IP to the masses.

Do you think the Simpsons NFT episode timing was a coincidence?

Disney acquired 21st Century Fox in 2019 which had the rights to the Simpsons.

Here's the TLDR:

- Disney is launching an NFT collectibles platform named Disney Pinnacle, in collaboration with Dapper Labs, the creator of NBA Top Shot.

- The platform is inspired by the physical pins sold at Disney theme parks, offering digital pin-inspired collectibles minted as NFTs on the Flow blockchain.

- Disney Pinnacle will feature digital pins based on characters and properties from Disney, Pixar, and Star Wars, including notable characters like Buzz Lightyear, Woody, Disney Princesses, and Darth Vader.

- Marvel, another Disney-owned IP, was not mentioned for inclusion at the platform's launch.

- Disney Pinnacle is specifically designed for mobile use, providing enhanced features and an updated economy design aimed at balancing accessibility for everyday fans and exclusive assets for collectors.

- The platform has opened its waitlist and plans to gradually onboard users for beta testing, with no specific timeline for a full public launch yet.

- Ridhima Kahn, Dapper's VP of business development and partnerships, facilitated the collaboration between Disney and Dapper Labs.

- Dapper Labs, known for its success with NBA Top Shot, developed the Flow blockchain for broader-scale consumer applications like collectibles platforms and games.

- The announcement of Disney Pinnacle aligns with recent signs of a revival in the NFT market, suggesting an upcoming wave of higher quality and more user-friendly NFT platforms and applications.

Buckle up - It's about to get wild.

- Disney is launching an NFT collectibles platform named Disney Pinnacle, in collaboration with Dapper Labs, the creator of NBA Top Shot.

- The platform is inspired by the physical pins sold at Disney theme parks, offering digital pin-inspired collectibles minted as NFTs on the Flow blockchain.

- Disney Pinnacle will feature digital pins based on characters and properties from Disney, Pixar, and Star Wars, including notable characters like Buzz Lightyear, Woody, Disney Princesses, and Darth Vader.

- Marvel, another Disney-owned IP, was not mentioned for inclusion at the platform's launch.

- Disney Pinnacle is specifically designed for mobile use, providing enhanced features and an updated economy design aimed at balancing accessibility for everyday fans and exclusive assets for collectors.

- The platform has opened its waitlist and plans to gradually onboard users for beta testing, with no specific timeline for a full public launch yet.

- Ridhima Kahn, Dapper's VP of business development and partnerships, facilitated the collaboration between Disney and Dapper Labs.

- Dapper Labs, known for its success with NBA Top Shot, developed the Flow blockchain for broader-scale consumer applications like collectibles platforms and games.

- The announcement of Disney Pinnacle aligns with recent signs of a revival in the NFT market, suggesting an upcoming wave of higher quality and more user-friendly NFT platforms and applications.

Buckle up - It's about to get wild.

RT @AcalaNetwork: Acala and @CredoraPlatform have teamed up to create an innovative and compliant lending vehicle for Bitcoin that uses Acala's liquid staking protocol #LDOT as the source of yield. 
                     
A significant milestone that brings an advancement in hybrid finance models 🤝

Decentralized Finance (DeFi) has made a significant impact globally by offering worthwhile yields, accessibility, non-custodial and innovative solutions. However, centralized finance (CeFi) continues to be relevant thanks to its regulatory compliance, customer support, and insurance offerings. During the last bull market, companies like Celsius and FTX ventured into Bitcoin lending without establishing a robust infrastructure to support their services.

This is where @CredoraPlatform stands out. Credora is a privacy-focused Credit Intelligence Platform with a strong track record in assessing creditworthiness and effectively minimizing risks. Credora has partnered with Acala to create a Special Purpose Vehicle (SPV) that leverages Bitcoin loans to derive a delta-neutral yield from Polkadot Staking through #LDOT. Credora chose Acala's LDOT as the preferred method for earning Polkadot staking rewards because of its consistent history, reliable infrastructure, and superior performance compared to other LST options.

The Special Purpose Vehicles are permitted to carry out only the specific tasks assigned to them, and these instructions are explicitly outlined and understood before the lender signs the agreement.

⛔No abrupt changes of plans
⛔No hidden credit risks
✅full real-time monitoring of loans

Additionally, within Credora’s framework, these SPVs are methodically separated both from a legal and technical standpoint. This careful separation ensures that all loans processed within this system are the sole claims over the assets held within the Special Purpose Vehicle. Moreover, these loans are part of the senior tranche providing an added layer of protection. These actions grant the SPVs ‘bankruptcy remoteness’, meaning the risk of them being drawn into bankruptcy proceedings due to financial distress are minimized. This strategic approach is projected to yield between 7-10% for secured loans, a significant improvement over traditional unsecured lending options.

Hybrid Finance (HyFi) has been quietly revolutionizing the way users interact with their assets in the cryptocurrency landscape. By fusing the innovation of decentralized finance (DeFi) with the distribution channel and compliant offerings of centralized finance (CeFi), it has provided a bridge for users to navigate the complexities of the digital financial ecosystem. Acala's #LDOT has proven to be a key asset in Hybrid Finance and it's will continue to play a pivotal role in driving the adoption and growth of this transformative financial ecosystem.

If you would like to participate in this innovative product, visit Credora’s official website at https://t.co/ZyHTvdpcmo 
If you would like to participate in LDOT directly, visit our Liquid Staking pool: https://t.co/clhExXgxf9
or stake on Euphrates: https://t.co/I0jlie1gYc

If you would like to build products atop of Acala’s robust and secure DeFi infrastructure, contact us on any of our channels.

A large network of bot accounts impersonating users like myself on X/Twitter has resulted in $305k+ stolen over the past few days.

🚨 Big news from us at @uncipheredLLC: We've publicly disclosed vulnerabilities in BitcoinJS-based wallets generated between 2011 and 2016.

The coordinated disclosure has gone smoothly so far. Vendors have notified over a million wallet holders! (please migrate your crypto from old addresses – don't be the 'I told you so' example!)

I was shocked by the amount of BTC in old addresses from the impacted timeframe. BitcoinJS wallets were very easy to setup which contributed to them having a large market share (and likely did a lot to boost crypto adoption). Note: estimating the total impacted amount is hard – there are large uncertainties on the estimates and a lot of nuance in all of this. Not that it matters. Please just migrate your old crypto before bad actors do it for you.

Not a BitcoinJS user? Still, move that old crypto! Private keys age like milk, not wine – the older, the riskier. 🥛

Migrating wallets? Yep, a huge pain in the🫏– I know because I'm in the process of migrating my own.
My strategy? I gifted myself a new laptop, new HW wallet and imposed a self-ban from using my old wallets on the new devices. When the urge to transact with an old wallet hits, I either use my old laptop or I transfer the crypto to a fresh wallet on the shiny new setup. 🚀 #Randstorm

RT @Hedgeye: 🚨4Q MID-QUARTER UPDATE🚨

In a 164-slide deck, @KeithMcCullough puts all our recessionary evidence on the table.

Newsflash: We're already in one.

"I got fired for having this exact same view in this exact same quarter of 2007. I was about to make the best call of my life.

Q3 2007, GDP was 4.9%.
What was it this Q3? 4.9%.

Wow ... When you have good numbers, you slow against good numbers. GDP into the Great Financial Crisis received serial large-scale revisions for years.

We’ve got a lot of cyclical data that’s already in a recession: Industrial production growth, manufacturing, hello.

It’s been a year of negative revisions for employment. Not a day, not a month, not two months. A year. We had seven negative revisions in a row in the Great Financial Crisis.

This one's worse."

As you know, this agency, which I had never heard of until 4 months ago, has been jamming up the launch of Starship. It has been a bit hard to discern whether this is the result of sheer incompetence, or something more sinister. In any event, this agency has been a real pain to deal with. 

As you know from my reports, I’ve tried it all over the past several months. I offered to put a tank of Goldfish on Starship and fire them off to Mars. I sent these bureaucrats a constant stream of donuts to try to win them over. I worked the back channels in D.C. I put a public pressure campaign on them. I filled out all their useless paperwork, including a detailed write up on the aerodynamics of a Starship versus a Starfish. All of this seemed in vain, and they ended up being a pretty brutal opponent. This goes to show that you can never underestimate the opponent. However, I kept pushing along all fronts and we seemed to achieve a breakthrough early this week when I was informed that the Fish People were beginning to change their stance. Apparently the pressure on these guys was starting to mount. I think I know what happened. They are currently involved in some drinking water scam in Texas, where they tried to deny water to 1.7 million Texans by classifying two completely unheard of Catfish species to “endangered” status. By doing this, they opened up a two front war, which is a classic mistake. Napoleon made this mistake by opening a two front war when he invaded Russia in the early 1800s. Germany again made this mistake in Russia during World War 2 when they pushed towards Moscow while in a fight with the West. Right as they were jamming me up on Starship, Fish and Wildlife got too big for its britches. They opened up a front against the two senators from Texas, who responded sharply to this Catfish situation. I believe the Fish People subsequently realized this mistake and decided to retreat. I’ve heard they are big proponents of Sun Tzu’s “Art of War,” and believed a tactical retreat was in their interest. Live to fight another day, as the saying goes. This is why we must remain vigilant. Fish & Wildlife has not been permanently defeated, but they are regrouping for another fight down the road. This is why I have no choice but to launch an effort to completely disband this agency.
